class Solution {
  public:
    int getSecondLargest(vector<int> &arr) {
        // code here
        int n = arr.size();
        int largest = INT_MIN;
        int sec_largest = -1;
        for(int i = 0;i<n;i++){
            if(arr[i]>largest){
                largest = arr[i];
            }
        }
        for(int i = 0;i<n;i++){
            if(arr[i]<largest && arr[i]>sec_largest){
                sec_largest = arr[i];
            }
        }
        return sec_largest;
    }
};

"Idea: 
  ### Idea Behind the Question

The goal is to find the **second largest distinct element** in the array.
First, we need to know the largest element because the second largest must always be smaller than it.
After finding the largest value, we again traverse the array to search for the greatest element that is not equal to the largest.
If no such element exists (all elements are same), we return `-1`.
This approach is simple and easy to understand using two passes through the array.

Time Complexity:- O(2n)                                                                     Space Complexity:- O(1) 
"
